## Design decisions

- Launcher = 12 lines of sh, ZERO logic: kit resolve + one fallback to the
  instance's vendored framework/qroky.sh via the machine trace. The
  fallback is 3 lines of path resolution, not duplicated behavior — it is
  what makes `qroky uninstall` work offline and after ~/.qroky/kit is
  gone (proven in scenario 22 round d2).
- qroky.sh entry «install launcher too» is satisfied by delegation:
  qroky.sh install/update exec install.sh, which wires the launcher —
  no second implementation (mandate: reuse ATOM-106/130 logic, never
  duplicate).
- PATH block profile choice by $SHELL (zsh -> .zshrc, bash -> .bashrc,
  else .profile); the DUPLICATE check spans all five common profiles, so
  a shell switch never yields two blocks.
- LAUNCHER_PATH_ADDED is set both when the line is freshly added AND when
  the marker already exists — the finale text is then identical across
  install/reinstall (keeps scenario 5 idempotency-diff clean and the
  message truthful: the line IS in that file).
- Foreign-launcher protection mirrors the skill rule exactly (provenance
  grep, honest «not ours to delete» line) — one doctrine, two files.

